The paper deals with a graph-theoretic approach to comparing road networks from different dates, which suggests that it could belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of databases and the analysis of the algorithm both theoretically and experimentally suggest that it could also belong to the Databases (cs.DB), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), or Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
